1
00:01:37,700 --> 00:01:39,170
(Episode 20, Fateful Meeting)

2
00:01:39,239 --> 00:01:42,170
Because I've already found a project...

3
00:01:42,239 --> 00:01:44,480
that can bring new development to IMU.

4
00:01:45,109 --> 00:01:46,510
If you're curious,

5
00:01:47,049 --> 00:01:48,209
I can announce it in advance.

6
00:01:48,810 --> 00:01:49,510
However,

7
00:01:50,519 --> 00:01:51,650
on one condition.

8
00:01:53,349 --> 00:01:54,319
What is it?

9
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,489
If the project is revealed...

10
00:01:58,989 --> 00:02:00,489
and everyone agrees to it,

11
00:02:01,260 --> 00:02:03,700
I wonder if Mr. Li has the guts...

12
00:02:04,299 --> 00:02:05,430
to resign voluntarily.

13
00:02:16,110 --> 00:02:17,439
I have a question for you.

14
00:02:18,210 --> 00:02:20,680
How did IMU manage to gain its foothold so fast...

15
00:02:20,909 --> 00:02:22,180
all these years?

16
00:02:22,310 --> 00:02:23,280
Isn't it obvious?

17
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,349
It's our products, of course.

18
00:02:25,419 --> 00:02:26,479
I think it's our tech.

19
00:02:26,650 --> 00:02:27,349
No.

20
00:02:27,650 --> 00:02:28,419
It's our users.

21
00:02:29,520 --> 00:02:31,090
When my father was still around,

22
00:02:31,189 --> 00:02:32,389
he told me this.

23
00:02:33,360 --> 00:02:35,990
"Give me peaches, I will return you plums."

24
00:02:37,199 --> 00:02:38,430
We trust our users.

25
00:02:38,629 --> 00:02:40,569
Our users trust us.

26
00:02:40,629 --> 00:02:43,330
That is why I paused Edge-N Project...

27
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:44,439
instead of aborting it.

28
00:02:45,740 --> 00:02:47,469
I thought you'd get the hint,

29
00:02:47,939 --> 00:02:49,469
sort out the breach...

30
00:02:49,539 --> 00:02:51,210
and improve user security yourself.

31
00:02:51,509 --> 00:02:52,210
Mark my words.

32
00:02:52,639 --> 00:02:54,050
It's about the safety of our users' info,

33
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:55,650
not our tech.

34
00:02:57,219 --> 00:02:59,050
Secondly, it's innovation.

35
00:02:59,550 --> 00:03:02,349
We do not prioritize imitating or buying someone else's tech.

36
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:04,219
Instead, we put innovation first.

37
00:03:04,560 --> 00:03:05,719
We were to gain a foothold...

38
00:03:05,789 --> 00:03:07,860
by using our tech from the fundamentals.

39
00:03:09,189 --> 00:03:10,129
Innovation?

40
00:03:11,199 --> 00:03:12,300
The word "innovation"...

41
00:03:12,360 --> 00:03:14,330
is music to anyone's ears.

42
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:16,770
So Mr. Lu,

43
00:03:16,830 --> 00:03:19,969
are you going to present a new and innovative project...

44
00:03:20,039 --> 00:03:21,740
that will impress...

45
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,680
old folks like us?

46
00:03:25,439 --> 00:03:27,280
To explore upgrades to our AI,

47
00:03:27,449 --> 00:03:29,810
we have intelligent humanoid companions.

48
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:31,520
As you all know,

49
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:35,750
I love researching novelties like these.

50
00:03:40,759 --> 00:03:42,389
Now, let's hear it...

51
00:03:42,460 --> 00:03:43,830
for the Companion Robot Team...

52
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:46,759
that created the world's first humanoid AIs.

53
00:04:04,819 --> 00:04:05,520
Hello.

54
00:04:05,719 --> 00:04:07,289
I'm the head of the Alpha Team,

55
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:08,319
Fu Yang.

56
00:04:09,289 --> 00:04:10,990
- We're going to introduce... - Mr. Lu.

57
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:15,060
Don't tell me your new project is going to be led...

58
00:04:15,129 --> 00:04:17,000
by a bunch of science frauds.

59
00:04:19,899 --> 00:04:20,930
Give us a chance...

60
00:04:21,230 --> 00:04:22,529
and we'll show you...

61
00:04:22,899 --> 00:04:23,870
if we're frauds or not.

62
00:04:51,199 --> 00:04:52,730
Hello, I'm Friday,

63
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:55,730
a new type of smart humanoid developed by Team Alpha.

64
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,000
With multi-sensor information fusion processors...

65
00:04:58,069 --> 00:04:59,470
and bionic technology,

66
00:04:59,540 --> 00:05:01,540
I am developed to serve humans.

67
00:05:01,810 --> 00:05:03,779
I am equipped with 20 deep learning capabilities...

68
00:05:04,009 --> 00:05:05,779
in human emotions, intelligent speech,

69
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:07,850
AI healthcare, fintech,

70
00:05:08,079 --> 00:05:09,449
and so on.

71
00:05:10,209 --> 00:05:12,250
Please enjoy Friday.

72
00:05:13,149 --> 00:05:14,920
This is just holography.

73
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,790
How do you pull it off?

74
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:19,189
Or rather, how did you not pull it off?

75
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:21,860
This is nothing but showboating.

76
00:05:22,089 --> 00:05:23,930
It's only a pre-recorded video,

77
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,529
and you call that...

78
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:27,829
IMU's core project?

79
00:05:28,269 --> 00:05:29,100
Lu Sen.

80
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:31,339
This bunch of frauds you hired...

81
00:05:31,439 --> 00:05:33,600
must have a lot of tricks up their sleeves.

82
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:34,870
What else have you got?

83
00:05:35,769 --> 00:05:37,040
Keep them coming.

84
00:05:39,139 --> 00:05:40,410
By frauds,

85
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,649
do you mean Team Alpha?

86
00:05:42,449 --> 00:05:44,279
Britain's most authoritative tech site...

87
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:46,279
has verified Dr. Fu's credentials.

88
00:05:46,420 --> 00:05:48,689
Friday has prepared the report for you.

89
00:05:48,819 --> 00:05:51,089
Please read it carefully and you'll see that it's real.

90
00:05:55,259 --> 00:05:56,189
Nice one, Friday.

91
00:05:56,329 --> 00:05:57,160
You did a good job.

92
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:58,560
You may go now.

93
00:06:00,930 --> 00:06:02,629
Alright. Goodbye, everyone.

94
00:06:17,050 --> 00:06:19,149
I'm sure that by now,

95
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:20,819
anyone who can read...

96
00:06:21,550 --> 00:06:23,149
can tell that Dr. Fu wasn't lying,

97
00:06:23,449 --> 00:06:25,420
in addition to knowing my prospects...

98
00:06:25,490 --> 00:06:26,360
for this project.

99
00:06:27,160 --> 00:06:28,560
If approved by vote,

100
00:06:28,689 --> 00:06:30,629
Team Alpha will be IMU's core project team...

101
00:06:30,699 --> 00:06:32,360
for the next five years.

102
00:06:32,759 --> 00:06:33,870
They'll contribute to us...

103
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:35,370
more forward-thinking technology.

104
00:06:36,370 --> 00:06:37,439
Now I'm asking you.

105
00:06:38,470 --> 00:06:39,139
Mr. Li.

106
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,639
Will you resign?

107
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:53,350
It's me.

108
00:06:54,250 --> 00:06:55,350
I failed you.

109
00:06:56,490 --> 00:06:59,490
I hereby announce...

110
00:07:00,459 --> 00:07:03,290
my resignation as Chief Operating Officer of IMU.

111
00:07:19,980 --> 00:07:21,209
We'll see about that.

112
00:07:23,449 --> 00:07:24,319
Just you wait.

113
00:07:32,360 --> 00:07:33,089
Li Er.

114
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,930
How did the shareholders' meeting go?

115
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,730
Did Li Jing Cheng give you a hard time?

116
00:07:41,399 --> 00:07:42,600
Of course he did.

117
00:07:42,930 --> 00:07:44,439
But I won't let him trample on me.

118
00:07:46,939 --> 00:07:48,470
You've got yourself a good partner.

119
00:07:48,610 --> 00:07:49,610
Even I as his girlfriend...

120
00:07:49,670 --> 00:07:51,310
didn't know about the meeting.

121
00:07:53,009 --> 00:07:54,480
That means you have good taste.

122
00:07:54,910 --> 00:07:56,009
You have a way with words.

123
00:07:57,079 --> 00:07:58,750
I won't bother you about work.

124
00:07:58,819 --> 00:07:59,850
If only you tell me the truth.

125
00:08:00,350 --> 00:08:01,819
I was worried sick out there.

126
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:03,720
Okay.

127
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,389
Actually,

128
00:08:06,189 --> 00:08:07,329
Lu Sen came prepared.

129
00:08:07,589 --> 00:08:09,689
It's still up to you and Friday.

130
00:08:10,699 --> 00:08:12,300
That's the Alpha I chose.

131
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,329
Lu Sen.

132
00:08:21,569 --> 00:08:22,769
Don't make me do it.

133
00:08:33,850 --> 00:08:34,649
Listen up.

134
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,490
I have something to tell you.

135
00:08:45,299 --> 00:08:47,100
I also have something important to tell you.

136
00:08:47,799 --> 00:08:49,570
But you have to pay up first...

137
00:08:50,600 --> 00:08:51,669
for this operation.

138
00:09:05,519 --> 00:09:06,250
Here.

139
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,059
Shan Shan,

140
00:09:11,559 --> 00:09:12,419
eat more vegetables.

141
00:09:12,490 --> 00:09:13,389
It boosts your immunity.

142
00:09:13,559 --> 00:09:14,490
Thank you, Uncle.

143
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:17,429
You're home early today.

144
00:09:17,929 --> 00:09:19,500
I just didn't have much to do.

145
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:23,399
So that's why you came right after work.

146
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:25,570
Here.

147
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:27,070
Shan Shan?

148
00:09:27,200 --> 00:09:29,070
Can I have one of your lights?

149
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,610
I want to give it to my tablemate.

150
00:09:33,710 --> 00:09:36,049
I'd like one too.

151
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:40,649
Your aunt and I like them.

152
00:09:40,950 --> 00:09:42,149
I can set up a unit.

153
00:09:43,690 --> 00:09:44,389
You see.

154
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:46,820
Well, our wedding anniversary...

155
00:09:46,889 --> 00:09:48,059
is around the corner,

156
00:09:48,360 --> 00:09:50,929
and I want to gift this to her.

157
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:52,629
So when I think of her,

158
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,029
she'll see it.

159
00:09:55,230 --> 00:09:55,899
Right?

160
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:57,970
Shan Shan.

161
00:09:58,070 --> 00:09:59,000
You have to charge him.

162
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,299
No more under-the-counter.

163
00:10:00,370 --> 00:10:01,139
Double the fee.

164
00:10:01,470 --> 00:10:03,169
Let's make a toast...

165
00:10:03,269 --> 00:10:05,080
for Shan Shan's invention, okay?

166
00:10:05,840 --> 00:10:07,039
- Here. - Cheers.

167
00:10:07,879 --> 00:10:09,309
- Cheers! - Cheers!

168
00:10:13,879 --> 00:10:14,620
Thank you.

169
00:10:18,720 --> 00:10:20,090
Lu Sen is busy with his work.

170
00:10:20,590 --> 00:10:22,490
I'm so sorry that he asked me...

171
00:10:22,659 --> 00:10:23,860
to treat you to dinner in his place.

172
00:10:23,929 --> 00:10:24,629
It's okay.

173
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:26,299
He's just like that.

174
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,230
We're used to it.

175
00:10:27,299 --> 00:10:28,330
No one is bothered, right?

176
00:10:29,799 --> 00:10:30,870
Watch how you eat.

177
00:10:34,539 --> 00:10:35,870
It seems that apart from work,

178
00:10:36,769 --> 00:10:38,110
he hasn't met us much.

179
00:10:40,110 --> 00:10:42,450
I wonder if seeing us reminds him of Friday.

180
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:46,879
And thinking of Friday makes him miss Shan Shan.

181
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:47,620
Right?

182
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:48,519
Indeed.

183
00:10:49,049 --> 00:10:51,419
He may seem better than before,

184
00:10:51,490 --> 00:10:52,559
but in reality...

185
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,889
You've been watching too many romantic dramas.

186
00:10:57,899 --> 00:10:59,830
I think Lu Sen has been quite upbeat lately.

187
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:02,870
Dear.

188
00:11:03,370 --> 00:11:04,669
If only you could pay attention to people...

189
00:11:04,740 --> 00:11:06,740
one-tenth as much as you'd do to a robot.

190
00:11:15,649 --> 00:11:16,879
Suddenly, I feel so full.

191
00:11:18,419 --> 00:11:19,649
Why don't we...

192
00:11:20,919 --> 00:11:21,820
take a walk later?

193
00:11:21,889 --> 00:11:23,450
No, I'm not full yet.

194
00:11:28,159 --> 00:11:28,860
All right.

195
00:11:29,490 --> 00:11:30,659
Let's go for a walk.

196
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:32,000
Look at my belly.

197
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,100
Let's go.

198
00:11:35,370 --> 00:11:36,399
I just remembered.

199
00:11:36,769 --> 00:11:38,639
Friday is going to IMU soon.

200
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:41,210
Shouldn't we run the whole program again?

201
00:11:42,639 --> 00:11:43,710
It will take you...

202
00:11:44,309 --> 00:11:46,509
five to six days to do that.

203
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:48,379
That's if it's done automatically.

204
00:11:48,850 --> 00:11:50,279
If the three of you run it separately,

205
00:11:50,610 --> 00:11:52,620
we'll be done by tonight.

206
00:11:53,649 --> 00:11:56,320
Then we wouldn't have the time to go to the bathroom.

207
00:12:03,289 --> 00:12:06,029
So what are you waiting for?

208
00:12:09,299 --> 00:12:10,029
I'm full.

209
00:12:10,230 --> 00:12:10,970
Let's go.

210
00:12:13,639 --> 00:12:15,009
Hurry up, Da Yun.

211
00:12:15,070 --> 00:12:16,970
The last one has to clean up.

212
00:12:25,149 --> 00:12:27,419
I knew you wouldn't give this for free.

213
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,490
Not bad.

214
00:12:34,730 --> 00:12:36,389
You're looking more and more like a leader.

215
00:12:37,330 --> 00:12:38,500
How absurd.

216
00:12:41,129 --> 00:12:44,029
Where should we go for a walk later?

217
00:12:44,639 --> 00:12:45,470
Come with me.

218
00:12:55,779 --> 00:12:56,450
It's good, right?

219
00:12:58,850 --> 00:13:00,120
No wonder you didn't eat at the dinner.

220
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,490
I didn't know there was such a good place.

221
00:13:05,659 --> 00:13:07,659
This is my secret place.

222
00:13:07,730 --> 00:13:08,860
I've eaten here since I was a kid.

223
00:13:09,559 --> 00:13:11,129
When my parents weren't around,

224
00:13:11,230 --> 00:13:12,330
I'd drop by here.

225
00:13:14,299 --> 00:13:15,629
I don't know why,

226
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,340
but when the couple who run this place are around,

227
00:13:18,840 --> 00:13:20,240
the noodles are exceptionally good.

228
00:13:20,799 --> 00:13:22,370
Maybe I could use some company...

229
00:13:23,009 --> 00:13:24,440
when I dine here.

230
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:30,549
What?

231
00:13:30,879 --> 00:13:32,649
You didn't know this side of me?

232
00:13:33,879 --> 00:13:35,919
You need to pay more attention to me.

233
00:13:36,919 --> 00:13:39,389
I have a lot of surprises.

234
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:47,100
R240,

235
00:13:48,230 --> 00:13:49,129
G235,

236
00:13:51,240 --> 00:13:52,070
B205.

237
00:13:54,639 --> 00:13:56,870
It's the RGB value of your favorite color.

238
00:13:57,679 --> 00:13:59,309
Your car and most of your clothes.

239
00:13:59,639 --> 00:14:00,840
They're all apricot-white.

240
00:14:01,049 --> 00:14:02,409
You're 170cm tall.

241
00:14:03,009 --> 00:14:04,320
And your shoe size is...

242
00:14:05,019 --> 00:14:05,950
It's 37.

243
00:14:06,679 --> 00:14:07,919
You never eat chopped onion.

244
00:14:08,149 --> 00:14:09,850
You're even less interested in Western food.

245
00:14:10,250 --> 00:14:12,759
You have a weak stomach so you only drink warm.

246
00:14:13,090 --> 00:14:13,789
And...

247
00:14:14,889 --> 00:14:16,860
you're a thrill seeker.

248
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:21,529
That's what I learned through observation.

249
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:25,740
